0 443 1207.0405 SECTION : Section A ; Page 1 ; Column 4 ; National Desk LENGTH : 880 DATE : December 8 , 1998 HEADLINE : Reno Rejects Outside Inquiry On Clinton for Campaign Ads WASHINGTON , Dec. 7 - Attorney General Janet Reno announced today that she had no reasonable grounds to seek the appointment of an independent counsel to investigate President Clinton 's role in a multimillion-dollar Democratic advertising campaign for the 1996 election .
444 547 Her decision swept away a lingering campaign finance issue that had haunted the White House for months .
548 861 On the final day of a 90-day review period provided under the independent counsel law , Ms. Reno concluded that no further criminal investigation of Mr. Clinton was warranted because there was '' clear and convincing evidence that the President and Vice President lacked the criminal intent to violate the law . ''
862 999 The conclusion was based on Ms. Reno 's finding that their decisions had been guided by legal advice that the advertisements were lawful .
