1043 1136 Ms. Reno did not reach any judgment on the legality of the advertisements ' financing itself .
1137 1328 But she said the laws that regulated them were ambiguous , noting that members of the Federal Election Commission just last week described the standards as '' fuzzy '' and '' hardly clear . ''
1329 1522 The commission is expected to consider at meetings later this week whether 1996 advertising campaigns of both the Democratic and Republican Parties amounted to civil violations of election law .
1523 1721 The $ 46 million television campaign at issue in Ms. Reno 's decision today was financed by the Democratic National Committee and , under the law , was permitted to convey only broad party messages .
1722 1883 Instead , Federal election auditors have found , it communicated specific electioneering messages that directly benefited the Clinton-Gore re-election candidacy .
1884 2148 It was as a result of that finding , three months ago , that Ms. Reno set out to determine whether an independent prosecutor should investigate Mr. Clinton or his aides on the ground that they might have knowingly evaded the law in directing the advertising drive .
2149 2458 During the course of the subsequent inquiry , in which Mr. Clinton himself was interviewed by the Justice Department , the President 's lawyers argued that his reliance on legal advice insulated him from a charge of wrongdoing , since , they said , it showed that he had had no intention of violating the law .
2459 2572 Today , in her filing with the special Federal court that oversees independent-counsel matters , Ms. Reno agreed .
2573 2825 The Attorney General acknowledged in that filing that Mr. Clinton and Mr. Gore had been intimately involved in the advertising campaign , raising money , formulating the advertising strategy , and reviewing and commenting on specific campaign messages .
2826 3010 But she found that their lawyers had also been deeply involved , so much so that '' media consultants periodically complained about the constraints the lawyers were placing on them . ''
3011 3108 At the White House , officials expressed their pleasure with the Attorney General 's judgment . ''
3109 3287 As we 've said all along , the President and the Clinton-Gore campaign complied with the spirit and letter of the law , '' said Joe Lockhart , the White House press secretary . ''
3288 3324 We are gratified by the decision . ''
